64M Set</a>, that will
help me write out my own programs (or so is the plan for the
moment at least) into cartridges and run them on the GBA!
While it arrives, I have been checking out some of the
cool and readily <a href="http://www.gbxemu.com/">downloadable GBA games</a>
in the absolutely fantastic <a
href="http://vboy.emuhq.com/">VisualBoyAdvance</a> GBA emulator. Really cool!
<p>
I need not buy a <a href="http://www.simputer.org/">Simputer</a> after all.
<p>
I am also upgrading my home PC with more RAM (+128MB), more hard-disc
space (+40GB) and a DVD-ROM/CD-R/CD-RW combo drive! Yay!
<p>
I might as well keep track of some of the sudden obsessions that overcome me
from time to time and that so many of my friends are so wary of.
